ative of Canada as a land of freedom at the end of the Underground Railroad.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Slavery.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311127380808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016z978311127630408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311141795040uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483230440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774832304423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774832304/original  a978-3-11-127380-8  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-127630-4  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-141795-0  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles